<FlowDocument xmlns="http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2006/xaml/presentation"  TextAlignment="Justify"   xmlns:x="http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2006/xaml">

<Paragraph>Essential Presentation library has support for converting the entire Presentation or a single slide to PDF.</Paragraph>
<Paragraph>This sample demonstrates how to convert an existing Presentation to PDF using our library.</Paragraph>

<BlockUIContainer>
<TextBlock Style="{DynamicResource HeaderTextStyle}"><Bold>Features:</Bold></TextBlock>
</BlockUIContainer>
<Paragraph>
This sample demonstrates the following features:
</Paragraph>
<List>
<ListItem><Paragraph>Convert all slide elements like text, shape, SmartArt diagram, table, etc., along with its formatting.</Paragraph></ListItem>
<ListItem><Paragraph>Convert RTL(right to left) text.</Paragraph></ListItem>
<ListItem><Paragraph>Convert with handouts option.</Paragraph></ListItem>
<ListItem><Paragraph>Convert the notes pages to PDF.</Paragraph></ListItem>
<ListItem><Paragraph>Option to include or exclude the charts while conversion.</Paragraph></ListItem>
<ListItem><Paragraph>Converted PDF document size can be optimized.</Paragraph></ListItem>
</List>
<Paragraph><Bold>Note:</Bold> This library supports creation, manipulation and conversion to PDF/image for .pptx format alone.</Paragraph>

